<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
So I'm camping to the right of the FM ledge in OT.  Been there for about 6 hours, watching my blue bar creeeeeep to the right.  Finally, I'm gonna get out of level 35 hell.  About 1 blue bub from dinging, Dragoon TVam kills in 4 or 5 swings.  That sucks... but hey, it happens, no problem.  I respawn about 30 seconds later at my spawn spot, just inside the FM zone.  I hear that "crinkle" that signifies I've respawned.  Unfortunately, I also hear myself getting beaten to death by Dragoon TVam again.  I finally get to the view screen in time to see "You've been slain by Dragoon TVam."  I'm angry now, considering I never got a chance to even run...<P>I respawn again, and the same thing happens.  I have now been killed 3 times by the same NPC without even being given the chance to *see* myself get pummeled, muchless defend myself.  I unplug the computer.  I relog and /petition thinking this should be a pretty easy situation to reslove.  They will certainly rez my experience for the second and third kill.  Not only did that not happen, but the GM was rude and would not even take the time to explain to me WHY he wouldn't/couldn't do the Rez.  <P>I'm sure there is some sort of excuse, masked as part of the Vision™, that stops GM's from rezzing in this situation.  I just want to make sure that the same company that banishes accounts when opportunistic PC's fear mobs into walls because of Verant's pathing errors also refuse to rez players that are spawn-camped by their own opportunistic NPC's.<P>I'd love to hear Abashi, Baelish or anyone else representing VI comment on this issue.  It's not that I'm blind... no one camps the Goons, they're there to kill you when you're not prepared so you'll lose exp, thus forcing you to play the game longer, spend more money, blah, blah freakin' blah, etc, etc, etc.  It's the same in many other zones.  I accept that.  I do not except getting screwed because I got spawn camped.<P>I play the game fairly and have excepted every nerf, change and expansion that VI has forced upon me and every other player.  In the scheme of things, my $10 a month means nothing, thus the reason I can be mistreated with no one thinking anything of it.  But if this issue does not get resolved in a fiar manner, you can be sure that you will lose my account and the accounts of some of my friends.  It's a competitive market out there for MMORPG's and there are plenty others to play.<P>------------------<BR>Helioluna Gladestalker<BR>lvl 35 Druid, Veeshan<BR>Shadow of the Darkness
</FONT>
