<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I sympathise with the exp lost - especially in a hell, but what a damn dumb place to bind!  If you play in Overthere for more than a few hours, you KNOW that people will drag the dragoons down the Valley towards Frontier Mountains and you KNOW this is an uttery dumb place to bind.<P>If you want to bind near the FM zone, then bind right up the side of the slopes, the dragoons have diffuculty seeing you up there.  You should also be aware that they often stick around for several minutes after being trained to the zone before walking back (slowly).<P>Like I say, sorry you lost exp, but this is how you learn to chose you bind spots with more care.<P>Shanya, lvl 49, Innoruuk Server
