<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The only safe place to bind is in a city where you have good faction.  If you choose to bind somewhere else, that is your choise and you take upon youself the risks.  If you are bound at the spot where a mob killed you, you're just SOL and you should have chosen a better place to bind.  Like on the other side of the zone, which is where I bound when fighting in the OT for just this reason.<P>Think on the bright side.  You could have been like the lvl 48 on the Karana server who fell asleep at they keyboard bound right next to the entrance at guk.  He was down to lvl 44 before someone in my guild came along and managed to petition to have a GM kick him so he wouldn't loose any more XP.  We only found out about the massive XP loss he had after he loged on another day and my guild mate asked him how much he had lost.<P>Think twice about where you choose to bind!
</FONT>
