Well, I'll have to agree, my bind spot was not the best.  Although, I bound myself literally a step inside the zone line so if needed, I could gate and take a step back and zone out.  I disagree with the idea that I need to bind in a city area.  I've managed to bind myself successfully without dying on a respawn for 36 levels.  I generally do not bind at zone area, that *was* a bad idea.  But if you take care that you've bound yourself out of the general path of the mobs your camping, you'll be fine.  <P>Again, my big ***** with this entire situation is that something needs to be done about how slowly the server reacts to players respawn.  I'm sure with all this technology, the mob can be kept from detecting me until MY screen populates.  I don't think this is asking too much.  If that would have happened, I would not have died more than once and the game would have worked as intended.  (Or at least how is SHOULD).  <P>In the long run, it doesn't matter.  I got o level 36 last night in OT anyway, albeit with an additional 4 hours of unnecessary camping.  Unfortunately, the zone is a big enough risk without the Goons running around and I will certainly think twice about camping there in the future.  <P>Indeed, there can be no reward without risk, but as I mentioned in an earlier post, I am no longer able to outrun most of the mobs in any zone, even with sow or greater wolfie engaged.  I don't remember lions or bears being able to catch me with sow on, but they do now, and routinely.  Yes, I'm running, and no, I'm not encumbered.  Explain that one.  The Troll GM that raced and beat me in OT couldn't.  <P>I love the game and I'll continue playing because I've put over 550 hours into this character.  But things other than nerfs and enhancements need to be addressed here.  <P>In closing, I insist I should have been granted the exp Rez because of the cirumstances of my deaths.  Furthermore, I picked a dumb place to bind, so perhaps that equals it out.  <P>Everyone goes away happy?<BR>-----------------------<BR>Helioluna Gladestalker<BR>36 Druid<BR>Shadow of the Darkness
