<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Having died from the goons once myself, I am sympathetic to your situation.  However, I totally agree with everyone else regarding your bind spot.  You should not have bound there knowing the goons were around (and if you didn't know they were there, oh well).  When I'm in OT, I bind in the FM zone, not the OT zone.  <P>Even without goons, people can train other aggro things to that zone line that will kill you.  I've seen druids quad kite back there, zone when they run out of mana, and the 4 MoB's then sneak up behind a group, kill the cleric in 10 seconds, and the entire group gets wiped out.<P>However, maybe I can help you with your understanding of this.  The world, for you, pauses when you zone.  You don't get updates, because you are loading a new graphics set.  If you are zoning, and you pop in a significant amount of time before your screen catches up, then it is mainly a problem on your end.  I see people pop and and start immediatly moving around, no delay.<P>If you are getting a delay, you need to compensate for it by providing yourself with a safety factor.  Hardware, software, and internet restrictions cannot be compenstated for by Verant.  By level 35, you should know your delays in zoning, and that zoneing into some places can be dangerous.  I would have been very surprised to see them exp rez you.<P>The only exp rez I've seen for a bind/multiple kill incident that didn't involve a bug is when someone thought it would be funny to levitate from a kelethin platform and bind in midair, then died an hour later, and lost 6 levels from falling.  I'm sure the Guide's had a good laugh and took pity on the fool, and called it 'a bug' and gave him his exp back.  <IMG SRC="http://forums.castersrealm.com/eq/wink.gif">
