<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Wait until you get a little higher and start to have to overcome some of the terrain and zones.  The only portal point for the WHOLE of Kunark is Dreadlands, now take going from Dreadlands to Overthere as an example:<P>The druid ring is right down the end of the zone, the zone point to Frontier Mountains where you need to head is a good 6 or 7 minutes away with SoW and Levitate on (the terrian is somewhat bumpy).  If you are at the lower end of the levels that hunt in Overthere, then many things see through your invis, many things double and triple hit for 100+ dmg, some things have SoW and Root and DoT's you.  Not a good place to run through if you can avoid it, especially when the dragon is being attacked, wipes out its attackers and goes on a rampage attacking anything it see's.<P>Next in Frontier Mountains.  Fairly safe to get through, but its incredible mountainour and going through in a straight line isn't possible, SoW, Invis and Levitate needed here also as there are some really annoying casting goblins in this zone that pack quite a punch (knocking out a HP bubble with one cast in lvl 30's). Average time to get around about is another 6-7 minutes to get into Overthere.<P>On top factor things, factor in the cost to teleport to Dreadlands (300 mana), SoW's, Levitate (batwings), Invis to get through DL, the same to get through Frontier Mountain, time to zone and you are looking at alot of wasted resources as opposed to making this trip once and just binding somewhere safe in the zone.<P>At lvl 19 you could be fighting in Lake of Ill Omen (great exp there), and even if you could get a wiz/druid to port you to Dreadlands, getting to the Lake means going through Dreadlands into Frontier Mountains then into the Lake of Ill Omen.<P>Shanya, lvl 49, Innoruuk.
</FONT>
