Sullon said:  Call me silly, but a level 19 druid should never need to bind again.<P>Ok.  I'm gonna call you silly.  On top of the 20 minutes of time it would take (at best) to run to OT from DL, keep in mind that Gladestalker was killed.  Thus, unless he had the foresight to stash some batwings in the bank, he will be unable to levitate.  Bad.  He has no armor or weapons...pretty bad, especially if you cannot root the nasty mob that saw through camo if it is too high of a level for you.  Even on the odd chance that nothing sees you, it is still damn scary to run through three treacherous zones all naked like the day you were created. =P<P>This situation is even worse on Velious, where the zones are enormous, where mobs have a large aggro range, where there are enormous cliffs that you can fall off of and die (since you have no AC at all now) and where the mobs hit like Mack trucks.<BR>Adding insult to injury, by not binding in a safe spot nearby, you have now inconvenienced your group for 20 odd minutes, which a caster type should not have to do under most circumstances.<P>The real point, though, is that there is nothing the GMs can, or should, do in Gladestalker's situation.  Due to the fact that my ISP is no good...grumble grumble...I have died several times due to lag, but this is widely known as something the GMs will not do anything about.  Computer handshaking is not instantaneous, and just because you get the LOADING PLEASE WAIT message (phew, I zoned with 1/2 a bub of hp left. wow...) doesn't mean the server received the same information, and there's simply no way for the GM to verify the information that you received on your end.<P>Don't bind in a point where all the trains are dragged to bud =)  Just a bit of advice from someone who has done plenty of really stupid things in my EQ career.  Live and learn.<P>Kolnar<BR>Druid of the 48th circle.  You will not evade me!! 49!!
